      <pubDate>Fri, 08 Aug 2025 11:05:30 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning. You're reading the Up First newsletter. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news" target="_blank"&gt;Subscribe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here to get it delivered to your inbox, and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/510318/up-first/" target="_blank"&gt;listen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to the Up First podcast for all the news you need to start your day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's top stories&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Israel's Security Cabinet voted early today to authorize the military to expand the war in Gaza and take control of Gaza City. &lt;/strong&gt;This area is one of the last remaining territories not yet fully under military occupation. According to the United Nations, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/08/nx-s1-5495694/israel-gaza-military-escalation" target="_blank"&gt;90% of Gaza is already under military control&lt;/a&gt; or off-limits to Palestinians. The aim of the plan is to disarm Hamas, get hostages back and establish Israeli security control of Gaza before ending the conflict, according to Israeli officials. Before the cabinet meeting, Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu told Fox News that Israel intends to take over Gaza, but not keep it.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-81622" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6124;         --source-height: 3445;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6124x3445+0+319/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F29%2Fde%2F23a21c204d53994f25758f7e9194%2Fap25219402587255.jpg" class="img" alt="Palestinians rush to collect humanitarian aid airdropped by parachutes into Gaza City on Aug. 7, 2025." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Palestinians rush to collect humanitarian aid airdropped by parachutes into Gaza City on Aug. 7, 2025.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Jehad Alshrafi/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;Public opinion on the decision is split. Many Israelis want the war to end&lt;/strong&gt;, NPR's Emily Feng tells &lt;em&gt;Up First&lt;/em&gt;. Some of the most forceful opposition comes from the military. But right-wing Israelis support the expansion. Former peace negotiator Menachem Klein says the Israeli army &lt;a href="http://one.npr.org/i/1257040914:x" target="_blank"&gt;cannot defeat a guerrilla force&lt;/a&gt; in its own territory. Mahmoud Abdel Salam Ahmed, who is preparing to flee Gaza City, says this plan is the worst news he has heard since the beginning of the war.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vice President Vance traveled to Indiana yesterday to discuss redistricting with Republican state leaders. &lt;/strong&gt;The battle to redraw new districts to ensure that Republicans win more Congressional seats next year started in Texas. The fight continues to escalate as Texas Democrats remain out of the state to try to block the GOP-led redrawing of the congressional map. GOP leaders, in response, have issued civil arrest warrants for the fleeing Democrats. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;Vance's discussion about redistricting signals that the White House does not intend to lose the political arms race&lt;/strong&gt; and wants to stack the deck in their favor, says NPR's Ashley Lopez. Among Republican controlled states, Ohio needs a new map because of state law. Florida's House speaker announced yesterday a new redistricting committee, and the White House has reached out to Missouri about redistricting. Democratic states have responded by &lt;a href="http://one.npr.org/i/1257040914:x" target="_blank"&gt;looking into ways to draw more&lt;/a&gt; favorable seats for themselves in case GOP-led states are able to redraw their maps.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;President Trump instructed his administration yesterday to develop a "new" census plan that would exclude &lt;/strong&gt;millions of people living in the U.S. without legal status. This would be an &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/07/nx-s1-5265650/new-census-trump-immigrants-counted" target="_blank"&gt;unprecedented change to how the country has&lt;/a&gt; collected population data since its first census in 1790. The census numbers play a significant role in determining how the president and congressional members are elected. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;The president attempted to exclude U.S. residents without legal status during the 2020 census, but failed&lt;/strong&gt;, NPR's Hansi Lo Wang notes. Preparations for the 2030 census are underway and no president can just order a new one. Congress has final authority over the census. Republican Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene has &lt;a href="http://one.npr.org/i/1257040914:x" target="_blank"&gt;proposed a new bill that calls for&lt;/a&gt; a new census, a redistribution of House seats and a round of congressional redistricting before next year's midterm elections. The bill would attempt to exclude people living in the states without U.S. citizenship, including green card holders, and U.S. residents without legal status. Lo Wang says that if the bill or any similar bills became law, they would likely face lawsuits.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Former Jan. 6 defendant Jared Wise is working as a senior adviser for the Department of Justice&lt;/strong&gt; less than five years after urging rioters to "kill" police at the Capitol. NPR &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/07/nx-s1-5493197/doj-trump-jan-6-defendant-jared-wise-capitol-riot" target="_blank"&gt;obtained police bodycam footage of Wise berating officers&lt;/a&gt; and the transcript of his testimony, in which he tried to explain his actions. Wise was not convicted of any crimes related to Jan. 6, due to Trump's order to end all Capitol riot prosecutions.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's listen&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resnx-s1-9399220" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 5333;         --source-height: 3000;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5333x3000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F11%2Fd7%2F8a8a17024791901c551a7ab85681%2Ff4ce7f15-ea57-4589-b967-7bd5a016d11e.jpg" class="img" alt="Why are people over 50 eager to re-enter the dating pool?" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Overall divorce rates are down except for one key demographic: people over 50. This phenomenon is called gray divorce. As we get older, it's common to hear about how much harder it is to make friends or build new relationships. But Gen Xers spent most of their adulthood living in a society where divorce is viewed as more acceptable and less stigmatized. That's one reason why they're open to starting new chapters. In this episode of &lt;em&gt;It's Been A Minute&lt;/em&gt;, host Brittany Luse &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5494232:nx-s1-9399221" target="_blank"&gt;discusses gray divorce&lt;/a&gt; and how it's never too late to write a new love story.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Weekend picks&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-79458" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4425;         --source-height: 2489;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4425x2489+0+277/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F4a%2F840e25164a3c8b63355883bd9515%2F20250715-dsc1538-edit.jpg" class="img" alt="Big Freedia on the steps outside of Esplanade Studios in New Orleans, which was converted from a church, on July 15, 2025." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Big Freedia poses for a portrait on July 15 at Esplanade Studios in New Orleans, LA. The studio was converted from a church.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Claire Harbage/NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out what &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/culture/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; is watching, reading and listening to this weekend:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍿 Movies:&lt;/strong&gt; In the horror film &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5299179:nx-s1-9395906" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Together&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, Alison Brie and Dave Franco play a couple whose bodies start fusing together after they visit a mysterious cave. The film explores toxic codependency.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📺 TV:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;Wednesday&lt;/em&gt; is back for a second season this week. To help prepare for the new episodes, &lt;em&gt;Pop Culture Happy Hour&lt;/em&gt; &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5492150:nx-s1-9396551" target="_blank"&gt;revisits their conversation about Wednesday Addams&lt;/a&gt;, who moves from her home to the gloomy Nevermore Academy.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📚 Books: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/05/nx-s1-5491598/new-books-this-week" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Manga: A New History of Japanese Comics&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; examines Japan's eye-catching graphic storytelling style. The book chronicles the evolution of manga from its late 19th-century origins to its popularity today.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎵 Music: &lt;/strong&gt;Big Freedia's new album, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/05/nx-s1-5340730/big-freedia-takes-bounce-music-to-church-on-new-album-pressing-onward" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Pressing Onward&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, fuses gospel and her love for bounce music, which she helped popularize. NPR's Ari Shapiro speaks with her about how singing in church as a child &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/05/nx-s1-5340730/big-freedia-takes-bounce-music-to-church-on-new-album-pressing-onward" target="_blank"&gt;led her to this moment&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍲 Food:&lt;/strong&gt; Social media influencers are bringing back recession-era recipes to help people cook cheap, easy and filling meals. Check out some videos and &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/07/nx-s1-5477546/recipes-tiktok" target="_blank"&gt;try one for yourself&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;❓ Quiz:&lt;/strong&gt; I was so close to 100%! I missed one question, yet again. Can you beat my high score? &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/08/g-s1-81265/trump-fitness-test-democrats-texas-zoo-quiz-news" target="_blank"&gt;Test your knowledge&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-81503" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6016;         --source-height: 3384;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+316/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2Fb1%2Fbcf9efbe425c8f24464412b3b5af%2Fap19237159497112.jpg" class="img" alt="&amp;#039;Superman&amp;#039; spinoff TV actor Dean Cain at a convention in Chicago. The actor shared an Instagram post on Wednesday about his plan to join ICE and urged his followers to join too." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 'Superman' spinoff TV actor Dean Cain at a convention in Chicago. The actor shared an Instagram post on Wednesday about his plan to join ICE and urged his followers to join too.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Rob Grabowski/Invision/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Actor Dean Cain will be &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/07/nx-s1-5495436/superman-tv-actor-dean-cain-joins-ice-recruit-immigration" target="_blank"&gt;sworn in as an honorary officer&lt;/a&gt; with U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement, according to the Department of Homeland Security. He is best known for his starring role in &lt;em&gt;Lois &amp; Clark: The New Adventures of Superman&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The Martha's Vineyard African American Film Festival is now in its 23rd year, offering a platform for Black artists to showcase their ambitious projects. NPR's Eric Deggans notes that the event &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/07/nx-s1-5494472/marthas-vineyard-african-american-film-festival-obama-slick-rick" target="_blank"&gt;highlights works centered on Black life&lt;/a&gt; that few other festivals might recognize or encourage.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;New York City officials announced that the remains of three more victims of the 9/11 terror attacks were &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/07/nx-s1-5495481/three-more-9-11-nyc-victims-identified" target="_blank"&gt;identified using advanced DNA-analysis techniques&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
