/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6d%2F04%2F047da4504d29b2606b180620eb01%2Fgettyimages-2182115969.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3600x2025+0+125/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6d%2F04%2F047da4504d29b2606b180620eb01%2Fgettyimages-2182115969.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3600x2025+0+125/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6d%2F04%2F047da4504d29b2606b180620eb01%2Fgettyimages-2182115969.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3600x2025+0+125/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6d%2F04%2F047da4504d29b2606b180620eb01%2Fgettyimages-2182115969.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3600x2025+0+125/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6d%2F04%2F047da4504d29b2606b180620eb01%2Fgettyimages-2182115969.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3600x2025+0+125/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6d%2F04%2F047da4504d29b2606b180620eb01%2Fgettyimages-2182115969.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3600x2025+0+125/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6d%2F04%2F047da4504d29b2606b180620eb01%2Fgettyimages-2182115969.jpg" class="img" alt="A Boeing sign is pictured outside the Renton Production Facility in Renton, Washington, on November 3, 2024." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A Boeing sign is pictured outside the Renton Production Facility in Renton, Washington, on November 3, 2024.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Jason Redmond/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;About 3,200 unionized workers at Boeing facilities in Missouri and Illinois have &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/03/nx-s1-5491548/3200-boeing-workers-set-to-strike" target="_blank"&gt;gone on strike today&lt;/a&gt; after failing to reach a labor contract agreement.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The Krasheninnikov Volcano in Russia began erupting early yesterday &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/03/nx-s1-5491540/russian-volcano-erupts-days-after-quake-shakes-region" target="_blank"&gt;for the first time in centuries&lt;/a&gt;, just days after an 8.8 magnitude earthquake rocked the area.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Loni Anderson, known for playing the empowered receptionist at a struggling radio station on the hit TV comedy &lt;em&gt;WKRP in Cincinnati&lt;/em&gt;, died yesterday, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/03/nx-s1-5491584/loni-anderson-obit" target="_blank"&gt;just days before her 80th birthday&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
